*"I will lead the blind by ways they have not known, 
along unfamiliar paths I will guide them."*{Isaiah 42:16}{*"The sign of a permutation reveals its fundamental nature."*}{Augustin-Louis Cauchy}

*"In mathematics, the art of asking questions is more valuable than solving problems."*{— Georg Cantor}

content.content:
The **sign** (or signature) of a 
permutation $\sigma$ is
\[
 \text{sgn}(\sigma) = \begin{cases}
 +1 & \text{if } \sigma \text{ is even} \\
 -1 & \text{if } \sigma \text{ is odd}
 \end{cases}
\]
